{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8a3c730e-63f2-4780-bb03-3832b2a07146","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since there's no existing code, here's exactly what you need to do:\n\n---\n\n### Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` root element, pointing to your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\" SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is the single line:\n```\nx:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\nThis tells the XAML compiler to resolve all `{Binding}` expressions against `SettingsViewModel` **at compile time**.\n\n---\n\n### Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**1. Enable `$(StrictMode)` warnings as errors** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treats XC00xx binding warnings as build errors -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045;XC0022;XC0023</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `XC0045` | Property not found on the `x:DataType` type |\n| `XC0022` | No matching property for binding path |\n| `XC0023` | Binding path type mismatch |\n\n**2. Verify it works** — intentionally misspell a property (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`) and build. You should get a compile error instead of a silent runtime failure.\n\n**3. If you need to opt out** for a specific binding (e.g., binding to an ancestor or dynamic context), use `x:DataType=\"\"` locally:\n\n```xml\n<Label x:DataType=\"\" Text=\"{Binding SomeDynamicProperty}\" />\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n- `x:DataType` on the root element enables compiled bindings for the entire page.\n- Misspelled or wrong-type properties become **compile errors** instead of silent runtime failures.\n- Add `XC0045`, `XC0022`, `XC0023` to `<WarningsAsErrors>` to enforce this strictly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ef6084f3-1d18-45c0-9324-d4ef3ba8cae1","outputTokens":789,"requestId":"111A:2C695B:CB8A1E:EB73DB:69FE8501"},"id":"823b6531-1a05-4cfe-83d2-66c2d947197c","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:29.213Z","parentId":"aa990bd8-deef-499d-b27b-581e40205c4b"}
